OUR NEW MACRO FORECASTS 2019-2020



Despite the end of the tax cut one-off impact, the US GDP growth should be =
quite resilient in 2019

The Eurozone could be the big loser of the trade war and should suffer from=
 the political instability

China's biggest problem is not Trump. It's China

On our forecasts, the global growth should be stabilised thanks to an addit=
ional China fiscal stimulus in the first half of 2019

The Chinese-American trade tensions are structural and should continue to f=
uel uncertainty...

... which force central banks to stay =ABbehind the curve=BB


KEY TAKEAWAYS

*   The US growth acceleration is not enough to avoid a global slowdown

*   Xi Jinping reacts by loosening its monetary and fiscal policies

*   The risks associated with growing corporate debt should intensify as we=
ll as with the Eurozone

*   Implications:

*    Upside surprise on global growth thanks to the Chinese fiscal stimulus=
 in the H119

*    Downward risk on Eurozone GDP growth and on Bund yields

*    Gradual rise in interest rate in a persistent low interest rate world

*    Resilient GDP growth in the US

*    Upward pressure on dollar

*    EM sovereigns with high external debt, large current account deficits =
and low FX reserve are vulnerable


